# Refracto Bead — STM32CubeMX project file (summary)
# This is a reference summary; the full .ioc file is generated by STM32CubeMX.
#
# MCU: STM32G491RET6 (LQFP64, 256KB Flash, 128KB RAM)
# Clock: 8 MHz HSE → PLL → 170 MHz SYSCLK
#
# Peripheral configuration:
#   - ADC1: 12-bit, 1 MSPS, channels 1 (PA0/TSL_AO), 5 (PB14/TEC_VSENSE), 11 (PB13/VBAT_SENSE)
#   - TIM2: 1 MHz PWM on CH1 (PA1/TSL_CLK), one-shot on CH2 (PA2/TSL_SI)
#   - I2C1: 400 kHz (PB0/SCL, PB1/SDA) — OLED + BME280
#   - SPI2: 21 MHz master (PB3/SCK, PB4/MISO, PB5/MOSI, PA8/CS) — microSD
#   - USART1: 460800 baud (PA9/TX, PA10/RX) — ESP32-C3 link
#   - USB: PA11/D-, PA12/D+ (USB-CDC for DFU/flash)
#   - SWD: PA13/SWDIO, PA14/SWCLK (debug)
#   - GPIO: 4× LED enable (PA3-PA6), 3× button EXTI (PB8-PB10),
#           ESP_EN (PB2), OLED_RST (PB6), STAT_LED (PB7),
#           DS18B20 1-Wire (PB11), CHARGE_STAT (PB12)
#   - RTC: enabled for Stop mode wake timing
#
# Power modes:
#   - Run: 170 MHz, all peripherals active (~40 mA)
#   - Sleep: WFI, peripherals running (~20 mA)
#   - Stop 2: RTC on, SRAM retained, GPIO wake (~12 µA)

